==English==

===Etymology===
Probably comes from ''hornete'', which was used in both Middle Low German and Middle Dutch.  The word also corresponds with the Old English word ''hyrnet''.  Hornet is probably derived from [[horn]].

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /'hɔːn&#305;t/

===Noun===
'''hornet''' (''plural'' '''hornets'''}

#A large wasp, of the genus ''Vespa'', with a brown and yellow striped body and capable of inflicting a serious sting.

